<!-- grok-build-executor:start -->
# Grok Build as external executor

When delegating implementation to **Grok 4.5** from Codex / GPT orchestrators:

1. **Do not** use native multi-agent / `spawn_agent` and claim the child is Grok.
2. **Do** use `$grok-build-executor` after user approval of the task card.
3. Write task cards only under `%USERPROFILE%\.grok-executor\task-cards\`.
4. Invoke `scripts/invoke-grok-executor.ps1` with explicit writable paths / command prefixes and prefer `-RequireCleanIsolation`.
5. Treat returned JSON `text` as a lead; independently `git diff` and re-run the acceptance command.
6. Keep planning, merge, and completion authority on the orchestrator model.
7. At most one concurrent Grok executor until concurrency is forward-tested.
<!-- grok-build-executor:end -->
